summary:
I am a master inventor, creative thinker, problem solver and storyteller. I enjoy working on meaningful, complex problems in healthcare by shaping and leading research exploration. I thrive in environments which are open-minded, multicultural, and interdisciplinary, and which encourage learning as well as failure. My biggest passions are healthcare in low-and-middle income countries, start-up entrepreneurship, and the application of human factors to technology development. 

International exposure:  USA, South Africa and the Netherlands

Vast experience: 10+ years (biomedical field) and 15+ years (scientific research)

Proven results: 170 invention disclosures, 15 granted patents, 80+ patent filings and over 60 full-length scientific publications

• Spearheaded the development of a synthetic percutaneous aortic replacement valve by managing analytical, experimental and numerical efforts geared towards future commercialization of the bioprosthetic valve.
• Oversaw the redesign and upgrade of a cardiac pulse duplicator to improve the fatigue testing of prototype synthetic aortic valves.
• Supervised biaxial tissue testing experiments to characterize the mechanical properties of the bioprosthetic valve leaflets. 
• Guided Finite Element and Fluid Structure Interaction simulations of prototype prosthetic valves using MSC.Dytran.
• Formulated first principles based models to optimize chest compression mechanical performance during cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) and to assess the impact of mechanical ventilation on CPR chest compression performance.
• Provided guidance and mentorship to undergraduate and graduate students in the Biomedical Engineering Research Group.
• Facilitated interdisciplinary collaborations with researchers in allied fields from other institutions and from Stellenbosch University.
• Drafted grant proposals for research on prosthetic valve development , neonatal cardiopulmonary resuscitation and neonatal hydration.', 'title': 'Claude Leon Postdoctoral Research Fellow', 'employment_type': None}]}]
